File: Clover is applying for an interdict to end its employees' strike. The company also wants to stop workers from damaging its property. (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Striking Clover unions will hold a mass rally in Johannesburg on Saturday. The Food and Allied Workers Union and the General Industries Workers Union have been on strike for nine weeks. READ: Unions plan to intensify strike action against Clover Workers embarked on protest action in November over retrenchments. They also say restructuring has affected wages and working hours. READ: Clover Strike | Employer applies for end to strike Last week, workers marched through the Johannesburg CBD removing Clover products from shelves. Meanwhile, the company is applying for an interdict to end the strike.